title: For Sale:  M41 Carcano Rifle w/Accessories  Collector Grade NICE
postcontent: I bought this rifle many years ago because of it's super condition which isn't seen often with Italian Carcano rifles. I've displayed it off and on over the years but it's now time to see if I can find a new home for it. As you can see in the photos this rifle in in excellent condition. Right after the war the Italians did arsenal refurbishments to some of these rifles that were already in good mechanical condition then exported them, and this is one of those. It's the M41 rifle which was the workhorse of the Italian Military during WWII. The numbers match and the finishes on both the metal and the wood are great. Everything works as it should and this rifle is chambered for the 6.5x52 Carcano round some of which is included with the sale. Barrel/receiver is stamped FAT 42 and the bore is bright and shiny without pitting or corrosion. Rifle comes with an original WWII era leather sling in great shape, original oiler and screwdriver tool in good condition, a high quality but older reproduction bayonet that works perfectly and 14 rounds of Hornady Custom ammo plus an original box of 1942 ammo that contains 18 rounds. Finally there are 3 blued steel 6 round Carcano clips and one made of brass. This rifle is one for the real collector out there and I doubt you'll ever find another one any nicer. I'm putting it out there to see if there is any local interest and it won't be the end of the world if it doesn't sell. I'm not set up to ship firearms so I won't do it. Therefore it's pickup deal only in the Brandon area by a Florida resident who,is 18 or older. Price for the rifle and all the accessories is $600. I can only post 3 pictures but have more that I can send to a serious buyer.  Thanks for looking.
